isAnonymous

boolean isAnonymous()
Returns whether the type is anonymous or not. A type for which objects or pointers are declared is not considered an anonymous type. 
 struct Outer {
    struct {int a;}; // anonymous
    struct {int b;} c; // not anonymous
 }
